sentences: Cynthia Phelps (born 1961 in Hollywood, Los Angeles, California) is an American violist whose versatile career involves work as a chamber musician, solo artist, and orchestral musician.
Phelps is currently the Principal Violist of the New York Philharmonic, a position to which she was appointed in 1992.

In 1994 she received the Outstanding Alumnus Award from Thornton School of Music as "a Thornton graduate whose artistic or scholarly accomplishments both reflect the ideals of the school and have furthered the art of music."
Phelps is currently the Principal Violist of the New York Philharmonic, a position to which she was appointed in 1992.
She is a former faculty member of the Manhattan School of Music and is currently a faculty member at the Juilliard School.
She has recorded for the Marlboro Recording Society, and the Covenant, Nuova Era, Polyvideo, Virgin Classics labels, and most recently Cala Records where her first solo CD was released.
